# Frontend production build configuration.
#
# By default the frontend calls the backend via same-origin relative paths
# (e.g. /api/v1/...). For this to work in production the frontend and backend
# MUST be served from the same origin, with a reverse proxy (nginx/caddy)
# forwarding /api/* to the backend (default http://127.0.0.1:8010).
#
# If the frontend is served from a DIFFERENT origin than the backend, uncomment
# VITE_API_BASE_URL and set it to the backend's absolute origin, e.g.:
#
#   VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
#
# Remember to also set the backend's ALLOWED_ORIGINS to include the frontend
# origin so CORS requests succeed.

# VITE_API_BASE_URL=
